  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf \u0da9\u0db6\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca.\u0d91\u0dc6\u0dca.\u0db4\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "WFP shows Sri Lanka's impending food crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The latest data report of the World Food Program showed that the amount spent on food imports to Sri Lanka dropped from 130 million US dollars to 50 million US dollars per month.",
        "Also, prices of nutritious food and vegetables have doubled to five times higher than before the economic crisis, the report said.",
        "According to the report, the governments of Australia, Italy, Japan, and New Zealand, the United Nations Emergency Response Fund, private sector partners, and multinational donors have donated 20.74 million US dollars to the World Food Program for Sri Lanka.",
        "But to support 3.4 million Sri Lankans from July to December, the World Food Program needs 63 million US dollars and thus there is a shortfall of 42.3 million US dollars.",
        "According to the latest report released by the World Food Programme, Sri Lankans have become accustomed to buying food and consumer goods in very small quantities due to the high cost of food and consumer goods. The World Food Program stated that as a result, Sri Lankans have increased the number of times they travel to stores.",
        "The World Food Program pointed out that due to the restriction of fuel imports by the Sri Lankan government for the next 12 months, it may not be possible to obtain enough petrol for daily needs. The World Food Program said the service was also disrupted.",
        "The World Food Program indicated that 6.3 million Sri Lankans are still food insecure and this number is likely to rise. Also, the World Food Program noted that 6.7 million Sri Lankans do not eat an acceptable diet."
      ],
